Cool!  I&#39;ve found that the best way to learn is to write something 
myself.  I think of something that I&#39;ve been interested in doing lately, 
and write some code in that direction, such as a digital jukebox, a 
custom news aggregator, or a screensaver.  I&#39;m not intending to finish 
the job, but it helps me write code that I understand, since JUnit is 
the thing I&#39;m trying to learn.  If I try to learn using someone else&#39;s 
code, then I&#39;m never sure if problems are coming from JUnit or the other 
code.

Not only that, but once you have a little experience with JUnit, google 
for &quot;test-driven development&quot;.  That&#39;s fun stuff.  Good luck,

    David Saff

